Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum semi-matchings in bipartite graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The paper also mentions the reduction of the problem to the optimal semi-matching problem, which involves graph covers. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts such as matchings and covers, which could make it relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
